public class SlidingWindow {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {4, 2, 7, 1, 5};
        int k = 2;

        int sum = 0;

        // First window sum
        for (int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
            sum += arr[i];
        }

        System.out.println("Window Sum: " + sum);

        // Slide the window
        for (int i = k; i < arr.length; i++) {
            sum = sum - arr[i - k] + arr[i]; 
            System.out.println("Window Sum: " + sum);
        }
    }
}


Sliding Window is an optimization technique used for problems involving subarrays or substrings.

Instead of recalculating the entire window every time, we:

Remove the leftmost element leaving the window.
Add the new rightmost element entering the window.

This reduces the time complexity from O(n × k) to O(n).
